    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="140"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.516/366</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Cuban Minister of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cortina</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the American Ambassador in Cuba</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="63" xml:id="d140fn63">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Ambassador in his despatch No. 1910, April 20; received April 22.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-15">April 15,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>1.—With regard to the good disposition of the Government of the United States to
                    cooperate with the Government of Cuba in the establishment <pb facs="0155"
                        n="147" xml:id="pg_147"/> of a central bank of rediscount, with its
                    associate banks for agricultural and industrial development, the Government of
                    Cuba accepts with pleasure the promises of cooperation that have been made to
                    it, and in this connection proposes to submit to the consideration of the
                    technicians of the Government of the United States, at an early date, a project
                    of banking legislation and of financing for this bank, to the end that in said
                    project there may be found bases of an understanding between both Governments
                    with the object of giving to that institution the firmness and strength
                    necessary for its very important economic purposes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. M. <hi rend="smallcaps">Cortina</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
